<h1><%= chapter %>. CGI scripts</h1>
<p>If you have developed CGI scripts on another environment, you can run them 
with Karrigell without modification. <i>Warning</i> : in version 2.3.1 this only
works with the asynchronous web server ; support for other servers will be added later
<p>All you have to do is put them in specific directories. By default, use the
folder <code>webapps/cgi-bin</code> ; other paths can be specified in the
configuration file, section <code>Directories</code>, option <code>cgi</code>
